In this memorandum, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delegates authority to the Secretary of State under section 7070 of the Department of State, Foreign Operations, and Related Programs Appropriations Act, 2023. The President's delegation is made in accordance with the Constitution and laws of the United States. The Secretary of State is authorized to carry out the functions and authorities outlined in the Act. The memorandum also states that any reference to the Act includes any future amendments. The memorandum concludes by directing the publication of this document in the Federal Register.